   247	## Member Bank Account and Cancelled Cheque Metadata API (004J)
   248	
   249	`GET /api/v1/members/{member_id}/bank-accounts/`
   250	
   251	Rules:
   252	- Requires a session-bound bearer token and `members.member.read` under A-034; missing auth returns
   253	  `401 AUTH_REQUIRED`, missing permission returns `403 PERMISSION_DENIED`, and an unknown or
   254	  soft-deleted member returns `404 NOT_FOUND`.
   255	- Returns the standard top-level list envelope. Each item contains `bank_account_id`,
   256	  `owner_party_type`, `owner_party_id`, `account_holder_name`, masked `account_number` as
   257	  `{ "masked": "...", "last4": "...", "can_view_full": false }`, `ifsc`, nullable `bank_name`,
   258	  nullable `branch_name`, `verification_status`, nullable `cancelled_cheque_id`, nullable
   259	  `signature_verified_flag`, `status`, and `created_at`.
   260	- The response never serializes full account numbers, `account_number_encrypted`, or
   261	  `account_number_hash`.
   262	
   263	`POST /api/v1/members/{member_id}/bank-accounts/`
   264	
   265	Request:
   266	
   267	```json
   268	{
   269	  "account_holder_name": "Ramesh Patil",
   270	  "account_number": "123456789012",
   271	  "ifsc": "HDFC0001234",
   272	  "bank_name": "HDFC Bank",
   273	  "branch_name": "Nashik Road",
   274	  "verification_status": "pending",
   275	  "cancelled_cheque_id": null,
   276	  "signature_verified_flag": null,
   277	  "status": "active"
   278	}
   279	```
   280	
   281	Rules:
   282	- Requires `members.member.update` under A-034.
   283	- Account holder name, account number, and IFSC are required. Account numbers must contain at least
   284	  four digits. `verification_status` is limited to `pending`, `verified`, or `rejected`; `status` is
   285	  limited to `active` or `inactive`; malformed `cancelled_cheque_id` returns
   286	  `400 VALIDATION_ERROR`.
   287	- The stored row keeps only a protected token, keyed hash, and last four digits for the account
   288	  number. The create response is masked and `can_view_full` is always false.
   289	- Successful create writes `members.bank_account.created` audit metadata with member ID,
   290	  bank-account ID, masked last four, IFSC, verification status, signature flag, status, request/IP,
   291	  and user-agent. Audit metadata never includes full account numbers, protected tokens, hashes,
   292	  cheque images, or file bytes.
   293	
   294	`GET /api/v1/members/{member_id}/cancelled-cheques/`
   295	
   296	Rules:
