   102	masked last four, IFSC, verification status, signature flags, request/IP/user-agent. Audit logs must
   103	not include full account numbers, encrypted token contents, hashes, cheque images, or file bytes. No
   104	workflow events for simple member-profile metadata create/read.
   105	
   106	## Validation Rules
   107	Require account holder name, account number, IFSC, owner/member facts, and document ID for
   108	cancelled-cheque metadata. Reject malformed UUIDs and unsupported verification/status values. Mask
   109	account number everywhere except the protected storage token/hash/last4 fields. Do not invent bank
   110	verification-letter, duplicate-active-borrower, disbursement-blocker, or payment-initiation rules in
   111	this foundation slice.
   112	
   286	  `members.sensitive_field.reveal_denied`. Audit metadata includes member ID, field name, reason,
   287	  outcome, denial reason when applicable, request ID, IP/user-agent, and expiry on success; it
   288	  excludes full PAN/Aadhaar, encrypted token contents, hash values, and identifier-derived values.
   289	- Missing auth returns `401 AUTH_REQUIRED` without reveal audit. Missing base read returns
   290	  `403 PERMISSION_DENIED`; missing field permission returns `403 SENSITIVE_FIELD_ACCESS_DENIED`;
   291	  invalid field/reason or unavailable source value returns `400 VALIDATION_ERROR`; unknown or
   292	  soft-deleted member returns `404 NOT_FOUND`. Sensitive reveal writes no workflow event.
   293	
   294	## 004J Bank Account and Cancelled Cheque Extracts
   295	- 004J implements member-profile bank metadata only:
   296	  `GET/POST /api/v1/members/{member_id}/bank-accounts/` and
   297	  `GET/POST /api/v1/members/{member_id}/cancelled-cheques/`.
   298	- `bank_accounts` stores member ownership as `owner_party_type = member` plus `owner_party_id`,
   299	  holder name, protected account-number token, keyed hash, last four, IFSC, bank/branch names,
   300	  verification status (`pending`/`verified`/`rejected`), nullable cancelled-cheque FK, nullable
   301	  signature-verified flag, status (`active`/`inactive`), and created timestamp.
   302	- `cancelled_cheques` stores member FK, nullable `loan_application_id` placeholder, document ID,
   303	  protected account-number token, keyed hash, last four, IFSC, branch, verification status,
   304	  signature-mismatch flag, and created timestamp. Loan-application-specific cheque behavior remains
   305	  deferred until application persistence exists.
   306	- Responses expose only masked account-number metadata shaped as
   307	  `{masked, last4, can_view_full: false}`. Full account numbers, protected token contents, and
   308	  account-number hashes are never serialized or included in audit metadata.
   309	- Because `auth-permissions.md` has no exact bank-account metadata codes, A-034 records the 004J
   310	  assumption: lists use `members.member.read`, creates use `members.member.update`, and no new
   311	  permission codes are seeded. PAN/Aadhaar reveal, KYC, document, disbursement, export, and security
   312	  permissions do not grant bank metadata access or reveal.
   313	- Successful creates write metadata-only audit rows: `members.bank_account.created` and
   314	  `members.cancelled_cheque.created`. Read-only lists write no audit/workflow row, and create
   315	  actions write no workflow event.
   316	- Validation rejects missing holder/account/IFSC facts, account numbers shorter than four digits,
   317	  malformed UUID fields, unsupported verification status, and unsupported bank-account status.
   318	  Duplicate-active-borrower warnings, bank verification letters, signature mismatch resolution,
   319	  blank-dated cheque custody, disbursement gates, payment initiation, and bank-account full reveal
   320	  are deferred.
   321	
